FOODABEE Privacy Policy
Last Updated: 19/09/2024
At Bluebear Technologies Ltd. ("Bluebear"), we value your privacy and are committed to creating a safe environment for you and your child. This privacy policy explains how we handle personal information in our mobile application, FOODABEE
®
.
Please note that this privacy policy applies solely to FOODABEE. Other apps developed by Bluebear may have different privacy practices. For information on those apps, please refer to their specific privacy policies or contact us.
1. Who We Are
Company Name:
Bluebear Technologies Ltd.
Address:
74 Fitzwilliam Lane, Dublin 2, Ireland
2. No Data Collection
FOODABEE is designed with your child's privacy in mind. Our app does not collect any personal information or data from users. This means:
No personal identifiers, location data, or sensitive information is intentionally collected by us.
We do not track user activity within the app.
No cookies or tracking technologies are used by us.
We don’t knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13. If we become aware that we have inadvertently collected such information, we will take immediate steps to delete it.
Please note that Apple may collect non-personally identifiable information such as app performance metrics and crash reports. This information is used to improve the overall user experience and is not linked to individual users.
3. App Versions
FOODABEE offers two versions:
Unlocked Edition:
A one-time payment gives full access to all features with no additional charges.
Subscription Edition:
A recurring monthly or annual fee is required. Subscription fees are prominently displayed, and there are no hidden in-app purchases outside of the subscription process.
4. No Advertising and External Links
FOODABEE contains no advertisements.
Any external links are placed behind parental gated areas, ensuring they are only accessible under adult supervision. This helps maintain a safe environment for children.
5. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this policy occasionally. If changes are made, we will update the "Last Updated" date. We recommend reviewing this policy periodically to stay informed about how we protect your information.
6. Contact Us
If you have questions or concerns about this policy, please contact us:
Email:
privacy@bluebear.ie
Address:
Bluebear Technologies Ltd., 74 Fitzwilliam Lane, Dublin 2, Ireland
7. Your Consent
By using FOODABEE, you agree to this Privacy Policy. As we do not intentionally collect any personal information, no additional consent is required regarding data collection.
Made by Parents. We Strive to Protect Your Privacy.
Thank you for choosing FOODABEE as a safe and enjoyable app for your child.
